English: (There's something there. Is it a notebook?)
Chinese: （……？　好像有放東西……是筆記本嗎？）

English:
(I took a look through, but it's just complaints
about work and stuff about good-looking guys.)
Chinese:
（……快速看了一下，裡面都是寫
　工作的抱怨跟帥哥部下的事情）
Korean:
(……내용물을 대충 확인해봤지만 일에 대한 푸념이나
 잘생긴 부하에 대해 적혀있을 뿐이다)
German:
(Ich habe es durchgeblättert, aber steht nur
Gejammer über den Job und Zeug über attraktive
Kerle drin.)

English:
(I checked under the pillow, duvet and sheet, but
didn't find anything connected to the data.)
Chinese:
（雖然也想調查枕頭跟床單底下，
　但好像沒看到跟目標資料有關的東西……）
Korean:
(베개나 이불, 시트 밑까지 조사해봤지만
 목적인 데이터의 단서같은 것은 보이지 않아……)
German:
(Ich habe unter dem Kissen, der Decke und dem
Laken geschaut, aber nichts im Zusammenhang
mit den Daten gefunden.)

English:
(Phew... That's some strong perfume! There's
nothing useful here. Time to go!)
Chinese:
（嗚……香水味好重好刺鼻……！
　既然沒有要找的東西，就快點離開吧……！）
Korean:
(으으……향수 냄새가 지독해서 코가 삐뚤어질 것 같아……!
 목표는 없는 것 같으니 빨리 떨어지자……!)
German:
(Puh ... Ganz schön penetrantes Parfüm! Hier ist
nichts Nützliches. Nichts wie weg!)
